). Several of the above variables\nare intercorrelated and likely to have common interpretations. We performed a\nPrincipal Component Analysis, in order to find their significant independent\nlinear combinations. We also analyzed a possible bias: countries with low\nGDP-per capita might have less testing and we discuss correlation with the\nabove variables.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 May 2020 17:57:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 10 May 2021 22:16:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-12"}
