>8$ Gyr), metal-rich (+0.25 dex) stellar population, which is\notherwise not expected from our understanding of chemical enrichment in M54.\nThe overall derived stellar mass-to-light ratio of M54 is\nM/L$_{\\mathrm{V}}=1.46$ with a scatter of 0.22 across the field-of-view, which\nwe attribute to the stochastic contribution of a young, metal-rich component.\nThese findings provide strong evidence that complex stellar population\ndistributions can be reliably recovered from integrated spectra of\nextragalactic systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 May 2020 18:01:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-17"}
